Standard Group PLC is committed to accelerating digital transformation through Information and Communications Technology (ICT).  Group Chief Executive Officer Orlando Lyomu said as a media house, The Standard has been going through a digital transformation and the Connected 2022 Summit will play a major role in the digital connectivity in this era.  The CEO spoke during the Waziri Golf Cup at the Leisure Lodge Golf and Resort in Diani, Kwale County.  President Uhuru Kenyatta is expected to officially open the summit today and ICT ministers from Kenya, Uganda, Tanzania and Rwanda are expected to attend.  The summit started yesterday with the Waziri Golf Cup and the innovation awards, and will in the next three days bring together industry players from private and public sectors and academia. "At the Standard Group, we are happy to join these discussions that are critical in this era," said Mr Lyomu.  He said the summit brings together stakeholders to meet and discuss the future of tech in the country.  The Covid-19 pandemic has thrown emphasis on the importance of digital connectivity in today's lives and the Kenyan government has committed to accelerating digital transformation as part of its Big 4 agenda.  Safaricom is the platinum sponsor of the summit, among other sponsors in the digital world.Â   By James Omoro | 2 hours ago By Stephanie Wangari | 3 hours ago By Henry Githaiga | 4 hours ago By Fidelis Kabunyi | 5 hours ago